en implicitly, either as the set of assignments satisfying a\npropositional formula, or as a set of consistent evaluations of a sequence of\npropositional formulas. In both cases, we provide bounds to the complexity of\ndeciding if X is a (uniform) possibility domain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 5 Nov 2017 12:20:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Nov 2019 17:15:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 13 Aug 2021 17:10:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-28"}
