e gradients of the\nfeature size and particle density with distance steepen in that region. We\ninterpret the propagating polarized features with shocks and the observed local\nanomalies with the interaction of these shocks with a recollimation shock of\nthe underlying flow. Together with a sheared magnetic field, this shock-shock\ninteraction can explain the large rotation of the EVPA. The superimposed\nvariability of the EVPAs close to the core is likely related to a clumpy\nFaraday screen, which also contributes significantly to the observed EVPA\nrotation in that region.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 5 Nov 2017 14:07:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-28"}
